  <!-- Accountability -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--colour-neutral);">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="text-center" style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Accountability &amp; Transparency</h2>
      <p class="text-center" style="color: var(--colour-muted); max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto 3rem;">We are accountable to our member practices. Our finances are reviewed annually and our committee is democratically elected.</p>

      <div class="grid-2" style="gap: 2rem; align-items: start;">
        <div>
          <h3>Annual General Meeting</h3>
          <p>The AGM is held each spring and is open to all GP principal contractors in Manchester. At the AGM, members can:</p>
          <ul style="line-height: 2;">
            <li>Review and approve the annual accounts</li>
            <li>Elect committee members for vacant seats</li>
            <li>Vote on the levy rate for the coming year</li>
            <li>Raise any matter of concern to general practice in Manchester</li>
            <li>Receive reports from the Chair and Managing Director</li>
          </ul>
          <p>AGM dates are published in our <a href="/events/">Events calendar</a> and notified to all practices by letter and email.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Committee Elections</h3>
          <p>The LMC committee consists of elected GP representatives drawn from across the Manchester area. Seats are allocated to reflect the diversity of practice types and geographic sub-areas within our patch.</p>
          <p>Elections are held in accordance with the Constitution. Any GP principal contractor within our area is eligible to stand for election. Committee members serve a fixed term and may stand for re-election.</p>
          <p>Current committee members are listed on our <a href="/about/team/">Our Team</a> page.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

